.TH "COREDNS-HANZOAPI" 7 "March 2026" "CoreDNS" "CoreDNS Plugins"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIhanzoapi\fP - REST API for dynamic DNS zone and record management.

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The hanzoapi plugin exposes a REST API that allows creating, reading, updating, and deleting DNS zones and records at runtime. Records added through the API are immediately available for DNS resolution by CoreDNS.

.PP
The plugin runs a side-car HTTP server (default \fB\fC:8443\fR) alongside CoreDNS and stores records in-memory. The store is designed to be swappable for a persistent backend (e.g., PostgreSQL) in the future.

.SH "SYNTAX"
.PP
.RS

.nf
hanzoapi [ADDR]

.fi
.RE

.IP \(bu 4
\fBADDR\fP - the address to listen on for the HTTP API (default \fB\fC:8443\fR).


.SH "AUTHENTICATION"
.PP
Set the \fB\fCHANZO_DNS_API_KEY\fR environment variable to require Bearer token authentication on all API endpoints (except \fB\fC/api/v1/health\fR). When unset, all requests are allowed.

.PP
.RS

.nf
Authorization: Bearer <HANZO\_DNS\_API\_KEY>

.fi
.RE

.SH "API ENDPOINTS"
.RS
.TS
allbox;
l l l 
l l l .
\fBMethod\fP\fB	Path\fP\fB	Description\fP
GET	\fB\fC/api/v1/health\fR	Health check (no auth)
GET	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones\fR	List all zones
POST	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones\fR	Create a zone
GET	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}\fR	Get zone details
DELETE	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}\fR	Delete a zone
GET	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}/records\fR	List records in a zone
POST	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}/records\fR	Create a record
GET	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}/records/{id}\fR	Get a record
PATCH	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}/records/{id}\fR	Update a record
DELETE	\fB\fC/api/v1/zones/{zone}/records/{id}\fR	Delete a record
.TE
.RE


.SH "RECORD TYPES"
.PP
A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, TXT, SRV, NS, SOA, CAA

.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Enable the API on the default port:

.PP
.RS

.nf
\&. {
    hanzoapi
    forward . 8.8.8.8
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
Listen on a custom port:

.PP
.RS

.nf
\&. {
    hanzoapi :9443
    forward . 8.8.8.8
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
Create a zone and record via curl:

.PP
.RS

.nf
curl \-X POST http://localhost:8443/api/v1/zones \\
  \-H "Authorization: Bearer $HANZO\_DNS\_API\_KEY" \\
  \-H "Content\-Type: application/json" \\
  \-d '{"zone": "example.com"}'

curl \-X POST http://localhost:8443/api/v1/zones/example.com/records \\
  \-H "Authorization: Bearer $HANZO\_DNS\_API\_KEY" \\
  \-H "Content\-Type: application/json" \\
  \-d '{"name": "www", "type": "A", "content": "1.2.3.4", "ttl": 300}'

dig @localhost www.example.com A

.fi
.RE

